node.text:
#Repost @champandthetramp with @make_repost
・・・
LINK IN BIO —> This week on @champandthetramp we welcome @lancepalmer. Lance is an absolute stud of a wrestler who started wrestling with his brother at age 9. He was a standout in Highschool and went on to compete at Ohio State University where he became a four time NCAA division one all American. 
 In 2011 Lance began his mixed martial arts career and in 2013 he made his World Series of Fighting Debut at featherweight which has since been rebranded as Professional Fighters League in 2017.  Lance won the PFL tournament in both 2018 and 2019 netting a million dollar cash prize consecutively both years. Lance was a great interview and trains both here in NJ with @Frankieedgar and with Xtreme Coulture in Vegas . Fight fans you’ll wanna check this episode out ! #champandthetramp

#Repost @champandthetramp with @make_repost
・・・
On today’s @champandthetramp we welcome to the show @leader_193 Errol Doebler . Talk about a guy who’s done it all, this guy has a resume that leaves nothing left to do. Errol graduated the navel academy in 1991 and served on both Seal team One and Seal team Four. After being injured on a seal deployment Errol had to re-examine his life’s purpose and calling as his injuries were substantial enough to not be able to continue his career in the seals. As if the Seals weren’t challenging enough Errol joined the FBI where he investigated international terrorist organizations around the world and shares some interesting stories from those years. After an illustrious 13 year career with the FBI Errol realized he was uncomfortable with the leadership presented within the FBI organization and decided to leave to pursue his true passion, teaching leadership skills. Errol is now the founder of Leader 193 and author of the book The process, Art and Science of leadership. Give this one a listen guys. I promise everyone can take something away from this interview. As always thanks for all the support and listeners.

node.text: You’re probably wondering why I am playing with random dog toys at my house. Well short story my friend, who is a tremendous dog lover, is utilizing her dog toy company @goodboystoys to donate some proceeds to AHS/Popcorn Park @ahspopcornpark here in New Jersey for Thanksgiving. This is a cause I can definitely get behind and I am happy to be involved. I have taken my kids to Popcorn Park over the years and they truly are a great organization who takes good care of animals in need. Check out www.goodboystoys.com to see all of their Thanksgiving boxes that come attached with a donation. I myself do not have any dogs but I have given some of the toys to my friends and their dogs rate them 10/10 would chew again 😂😂

#Repost @champandthetramp with @make_repost
・・・
LINK IN BIO —> This week on @Champandthetramp Roger and Frankie talk about the Jake Paul vs Tyron Woolley fight card.  They then move onto discussing how they both spend to much time on their phones and how that is misappropriating their time. It’s a vice for many of us and despite the many advantages of technology we also must admit the down side of it and how it take away from family time. Roger talks about his jump off Kingsman quarry in Maine when he was just 21 years old and how that one jump resulted in a life time of pain and issues with his spine and how it has had a profound effect on his left leg and specifically his calf which has atrophied away do to permanent nerve damage. Check us out on all podcast formats. Thanks for the love and support guys !

#Repost @champandthetramp with @make_repost
・・・
LINK IN BIO —> This week on @champandthetramp Frankie and Roger welcome Micheal Frank to the show. Mike has an all to familiar story to so many with his battle with addiction. We all have someone close to us who have battled addiction and many of us have lost loved ones to their struggle. Mike is brutally honest and forthcoming about years of addition to opiates and how it impacted him and quite litterly almost killed him from an overdose. He estimates he was in and out of 25 different rehab facilities around the United States all of which he relapsed after leaving. After hitting rock bottom Mike flew to Mexico high and was actually hallucinating on the plane ride there . He had enrolled in a Holistic/ Spiritual rehab program in Mexico as a last ditch effort to save his life. That was over a year ago and he has been sober ever since. Tune in and listen to what he experienced and endured during his stay at this particular rehab. It is like nothing you will ever hear at any other rehab anywhere else. #champandthetramp

node.text: Huge thank you to @bridgewater_acura for not only purchasing my truck but Dan over there made the whole experience about as easy and stress free as any auto sale I’ve ever had. No weirdos calling or showing up at your door. No tire kickers. A guy just shows up with a tow truck and a check. Check them out for all your car needs. They got it all. Including my truck! Which they will be happy to finance for you.

#Repost @champandthetramp with @make_repost
・・・
LINK IN BIO—> This week on @Champandthetramp , Roger and Frankie welcome @anthony_prettyboy to the show ahead of his fight this Saturday with @Tommyfury on the @jakepaul VS @twoodley on PPV. Anthony began his fight career as an MMA fighter with a record of 7-5-0 and has a number of amateur boxing bouts as well as one professional boxing match to his name. Anthony is the underdog coming into this fight but you wouldn’t know it talking to him. He’s a confident 30 year old ready to give Tommy Fury his first loss as a professional boxer. Boxing fans tune in and check this one out guys. #ChampandtheTramp
Summer time at the Shore.
